nodes.text: The Bothan Museum heist was a heist in a Bothan museum that was accredited to the female bounty hunter Kendoh Voss. In 34 ABY during the Battle of Batuu, Voss was accused of being behind the heist by a First Order stormtrooper sergeant, while on a mission to steal the hilt of the Sword of Khashyun from collector Dok-Ondar. Voss claimed that the culprit had never officially been found.
